comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-26T14:50:24.301Z",audit-agent,"AUDIT RESULTS SUMMARY (2026-04-26):\n\nOVERALL STATUS: PASS - All 78 test files, 1052 tests pass. CLI fully functional.\n\nDOGFOOD VERIFICATION (temp sandbox):\n- init: OK - Creates all directories, schema files, settings\n- config: OK - project/global scope, definition-of-done, test-result-tracking\n- health: OK - All 8 checks pass (settings, directories, extensions, storage, integrity, history_drift, vectorization, settings_values)\n- create: OK - All types (Epic, Feature, Task, Chore), all fields including rich metadata (risk, confidence, sprint, release, reviewer, goal, objective, value, impact, outcome, why_now)\n- lifecycle: OK - claim, start-task, pause-task, close-task, release all work correctly\n- update: OK - All fields update properly, history recorded\n- comments/notes/learnings: OK - Append correctly with author/timestamp\n- files/docs: OK - Link management works\n- append: OK - Body append works\n- calendar: OK - All 4 views (agenda, day, week, month), reminders and deadlines render correctly\n- context: OK - Token-efficient snapshot with high/low level items and agenda\n- aggregate: OK - Group-by type/status/priority works\n- list variants: OK - list-all, list-open, list-in-progress, list-blocked, list-closed, list-canceled\n- search: OK - Hybrid search with scoring and matched_fields\n- reindex: OK - Keyword mode rebuilds artifacts\n- history: OK - Full audit trail with JSON patches and hash chains\n- activity: OK - Cross-item activity log\n- deps: OK - Tree format dependency view\n- stats: OK - Project statistics\n- validate: OK - Resolution and history drift checks\n- dedupe-audit: OK - Parent scope deduplication\n- comments-audit: OK - Coverage reporting by type\n- contracts: OK - Machine-readable flag/schema contracts\n- search: OK - Hybrid mode with semantic weight\n\nTELEMETRY STACK (remote): FULLY OPERATIONAL\n- Endpoint: [redacted_telemetry_endpoint] returns HTTP 200 with proper payload\n- [redacted_datastore]: [redacted_event_count] events stored and queryable\n- [redacted_queue_service]: Healthy, message processing\n- [redacted_monitoring_ui]: v11.6.14, dashboard accessible at [redacted_monitoring_endpoint]\n- [redacted_log_store]: Ready, collecting container logs via [redacted_collector]\n- [redacted_trace_store]: Ready, receiving OTLP traces\n- [redacted_metrics_service]: Ready\n- [redacted_collector]: v1.16.0, configured for Docker log discovery + OTLP trace forwarding"
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-26T14:50:52.497Z",audit-agent,"FINDINGS - Issues and Improvements Identified:\n\n1. TELEMETRY TEST ROBUSTNESS (FIXED): telemetry-runtime.spec.ts was vulnerable to env contamination - PM_TELEMETRY_DISABLED leaking from parent shell caused 4/5 tests to fail. Fixed by clearing env in withTempGlobalRoot helper.\n\n2. SDK GAPS (existing items track these):\n   - No extension project template/scaffold (only inline docs examples)\n   - defineExtension is the only author helper utility\n   - Custom field/search/vector adapter types are Record<string,unknown> not strongly typed\n   - No deactivate/cleanup lifecycle hook for long-lived hosts\n   - No public SDK for host lifecycle (load/activate) for third-party embedders\n\n3. CALENDAR GAPS (minor, existing items track):\n   - No local timezone display support (UTC-only bucketing)\n   - No reminder recurrence (only events recur)\n   - No iCal/CSV feed export\n   - --limit is blunt global cap (can hide later days in month view)\n   - Two different CalendarEvent types (storage vs output) share same name\n\n4. TELEMETRY GAPS (some tracked):\n   - capture_level setting stored but not enforced in runtime\n   - retention_days setting stored but no local TTL cleanup\n   - No background drainer (queue only flushes on next command)\n   - No max queue size / disk cap\n   - OTLP trace/span ID encoding may not match strict spec (hex vs base64)\n   - No OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_HEADERS support for auth\n   - pm health has no telemetry check (docs claim it does)\n   - No CLI metrics for [redacted_metrics_service] (only traces via OTLP)\n   - No crash/last-gasp flush\n\n5. GENERAL:\n   - All community files present (LICENSE, CHANGELOG, CONTRIBUTING, SECURITY, CODE_OF_CONDUCT)\n   - .gitignore properly excludes telemetry data, search cache, .env\n   - Default telemetry endpoint in constants.ts is appropriate (public endpoint)\n   - No private IPs or credentials in source code"
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-26T14:51:14.872Z",audit-agent,"Key learnings from 2026-04-26 dogfood audit:\n\n1. The pm CLI is production-ready with 1052 passing tests across 78 files covering all features.\n2. The extension system (SDK + runtime) is well-designed but needs scaffolding tools for extension authors.\n3. Calendar is fully functional for agent use with 4 views, recurrence, reminders, and rich filtering.\n4. Telemetry pipeline is end-to-end operational with [redacted_event_count] events in [redacted_datastore], but capture_level and retention_days settings are not enforced in code.\n5. Test robustness requires explicit env cleanup - PM_TELEMETRY_DISABLED contamination caused false failures.\n6. The TOON output format is excellent for agent token efficiency.\n7. Remote stack ([redacted_observability_stack]) is fully operational.\n8. All community files present and .gitignore properly configured for telemetry privacy."
files[4]{path,scope,note}:
  src/cli/commands/calendar.ts,project,Calendar implementation audited
  src/core/telemetry/runtime.ts,project,Telemetry pipeline implementation
